Steps :
-> Schema design [SQL/ETL]
-> Data extraction and loading [SQL/Python]
-> Data cleaning [Python/SQL/Excel]
-> EDA [SQL]
-> Business Logic [SCM]
-> Simulation [Python]
-> Optimization & Testing [Python]
-> Dashboarding [PowerBI]
-> Deployment [SQL/ETL]

Stages :
| Stage              | Tool                          | Purpose                |
| ------------------ | ----------------------------- | ---------------------- |
| Data creation      | Excel / Google Sheets         | Initial tables         |
| Validation & joins | Power Query or Python Pandas  | Combine and clean data |
| Storage            | SQL (PostgreSQL / SQLite)     | Later integration      |
| Visualization      | Power BI                      | KPI dashboards         |
| Modeling           | Python (NumPy, Pandas, SciPy) | EOQ, ROP, simulation   |

Step 1 :
| Step | What You’ll Do               | Purpose                                       |
| ---- | ---------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| 1    | Read all Excel sheets        | Load data into memory                         |
| 2    | Verify schema                | Expected columns exist, correct dtypes        |
| 3    | Primary key checks           | Unique SKU, Supplier_ID, etc.                 |
| 4    | Foreign key checks           | Products → Suppliers, Warehouses              |
| 5    | Missing / null checks        | Detect incomplete data                        |
| 6    | Basic descriptive validation | Range checks (cost > 0, lead time reasonable) |
| 7    | Export clean CSVs            | Save to `/data/processed/`                    |
